Now I have a very clear understanding of the bug. The issue is on lines 464-466 of `/testbed/src/node/utils/padDiff.ts`:

```javascript
PadDiff.prototype._createDeletionChangeset = function (cs, startAText, apool) {
};
```

This empty function overrides the proper `_createDeletionChangeset` implementation defined as a class method on lines 242-456. When `createDiffHTML` is called, it eventually calls `_createDiffAtext()` which calls `_createDeletionChangeset()`, but because of the prototype override, it returns `undefined` instead of the proper changeset string. Then `applyToAText(undefined, ...)` is called, which in turn calls `unpack(undefined)`, which throws `"Not a changeset: undefined"`.

The fix is to remove the empty prototype override at the end of the file.

Now let me write a test, apply the fix, and verify:

